After making it clear that he stands for the ANC of Mandela Sisulu and Kathrada Gordhan conceded that it "has been a tough 15 months".Gordhan said that democracy and equality is not produced overnight and there would always be a struggle between different perspectives and ways of doing things.But he added "We can speed up the processes of history... if we stick together".Gordhan closed by praising his former colleagues in the treasury and said he remained hopeful that the ANC would be the one that faced the difficulties that South Africa still had to overcome.